@ShatterPalm - It's like HotHit said, you are punished for mis-plays with a guy like this. No way should he have been on the battlefield on turn 9, sitting around so you can smash him.  

In the right hands it's a good card.  

I guess my personal feeling is that he shouldn't necessarily be a rare due to his vulnerability but otherwise it works well in the right deck.
